Teach `sdk-event-mapper.ts` to read and forward the new `status` field on `system.status` messages while staying backward-compatible with body/message text.

**File**: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sdk-event-mapper.ts` (lines 115–125)

**Current code:**
```ts
    // Handle system status messages ("Compacting context...", permission mode changes)
    if (message.subtype === 'status') {
      const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
      const text = (msg.body as string) ?? (msg.message as string) ?? '';
      if (text) {
        yield {
          type: 'system_status',
          data: { message: text },
        };
      }
      return;
    }
```

**Target code:**
```ts
    // Handle system status messages ("Compacting context...", permission mode changes, 'requesting')
    if (message.subtype === 'status') {
      const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
      const status = msg.status as string | undefined;
      const text = (msg.body as string) ?? (msg.message as string) ?? '';
      if (text || status) {
        yield {
          type: 'system_status',
          data: {
            message: text || (status ? `Status: ${status}` : ''),
            ...(status ? { status } : {}),
          },
        };
      }
      return;
    }
```

Notes:
- The fallback `message` (`"Status: requesting"`) ensures older renderers that only read `message` still see something meaningful.
- When both `text` and `status` are present, both are forwarded; when only `status`, a synthetic message is constructed.
- Conditional spread for `status` keeps the event object clean when absent.

**Acceptance:**
- `pnpm typecheck && pnpm build` pass.
- Existing `system_status` event renderers work unchanged.
- When the SDK emits `{ subtype: 'status', status: 'requesting' }` (no body), the mapper produces an event with both `message` and `status` populated.

Cover the new status forwarding with a unit test.

**File**: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/sdk-event-mapper.test.ts`

**Test to add:**

```ts
describe('system.status with status field (SDK 0.2.108+)', () => {
  // Purpose: requesting status (no body) still yields a system_status event with status field
  it('emits system_status with status and synthetic message when only status is set', async () => {
    const msg = {
      type: 'system',
      subtype: 'status',
      status: 'requesting',
    } as unknown as SDKMessage;

    const events = [];
    for await (const ev of mapSdkMessage(msg, fakeSession(), 'sess-1', emptyToolState())) {
      events.push(ev);
    }

    expect(events).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(events[0].type).toBe('system_status');
    expect(events[0].data.status).toBe('requesting');
    expect(events[0].data.message).toMatch(/requesting/i);
  });

  // Purpose: backward compat — body text without status still emits a plain event
  it('emits system_status with message only when status is absent', async () => {
    const msg = {
      type: 'system',
      subtype: 'status',
      body: 'Compacting context...',
    } as unknown as SDKMessage;

    const events = [];
    for await (const ev of mapSdkMessage(msg, fakeSession(), 'sess-1', emptyToolState())) {
      events.push(ev);
    }

    expect(events[0].data.message).toBe('Compacting context...');
    expect(events[0].data).not.toHaveProperty('status');
  });
});
```

**Acceptance:**
- Both tests pass.
- `pnpm test:run` stays green.
